m and Islam, his influence on Nicholas of Cusa and his personality as an author of literary works. In addition various other aspects of "Lullism" are dealt with which cast light on the overall achievement of the Catalan philosopher and convey a vivid impression of his extraordinarily dynamic personality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Multiple languages.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aTheologyxHistoryyMiddle Ages, 600-1500vCongresses. 4aKongress. 4aLullus, Raimundus 1232-1315. 4aTrujillo ‹Cacéres, 1994›. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBadia, Lola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonner, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriesemeister, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColomer, Eusebi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomínguez Reboiras, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomínguez, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDomínguez, Fernando, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEuler, Walter Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHames, Harvey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHösle, Vittorio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLohr, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReinhardt, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuiz Simon, Josep Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalas, Jaime de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalas, Jaime de, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUrvoy, Dominique, econtr